en_549057_0	Undertaking the first field visit to the Security Force Headquarters – Central (SFHQ-Cen) in Diyatalawa upon taking reins of the Army, a few months ago Lieutenant General Shavendra Silva, Commander of the Army arrived at the SFHQ-Cen on Friday (6) in order to receive an update on the role and tasks of the Central Headquarters.
en_549057_1	The visiting Commander was saluted in a formal Guard Turnout soon after he arrived at the main entrance to the SFHQ-Cen after he was warmly received by Major General Laksiri Waduge, Commander, Security Forces - Central and several other senior Officers.
en_549057_2	A few minutes later, a Guard of Honour presented by soldiers of the Commander’s own Regiment, 23 Gajaba Regiment saluted him in the parade ground as the highest military honour.
en_549057_3	Minutes after receiving the honours, the Commander left memories by planting a 'Red Sandalwood' sapling inside the SFHQ-Cen premises.
en_549057_4	Afterwards, his visit was made further memorable after he was invited to sit for a group photograph.
en_549057_5	After a break, the Commander as has been the practice, addressed the Officers and Other Ranks drawn from all Divisions, Brigades and Battalions where he commended the troops at the Nelum Pokuna Auditorium, Sri Lanka Military Academy and highlighted the Army welfare projects and his vision with those projects.
en_549057_6	Further the Commander of the Army stated that each soldier should gain the professional specialization and must maintain the higher standard of discipline during the service.
en_549057_7	He also took time off speak to the Officers of Divisions, Brigades and all formations under command to the SFHQ-Cen.
en_549057_8	After the troops address the Commander of the Army and Commander, SF-Cen exchanged mementos as the day’s memories.
en_549057_9	Afterwards, the Commander of the Army joined All Ranks for refreshments and shared a few thoughts with the gathering.
en_549057_10	Before his departure he left his signature in the SFHQ-Cen Visitors’ Book.
